needed to save every month,

98
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:45,210
every week, or even every day,

99
00:03:45,210 --> 00:03:47,740
everything seemed much more achievable.

100
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:50,970
I knew that if I hit my
savings targets every week

101
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:52,880
then I would achieve my vision.

102
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,500
These are called process targets

103
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:58,270
and they're great is they
allow you to take small steps

104
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:00,100
towards a big vision.

105
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,550
The only thing that could
stop me now was myself.

106
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:04,620
So I need to set some rules.

107
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:06,360
I fully committed to these rules,

108
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,261
and I printed them out and I stuck them

109
00:04:08,261 --> 00:04:09,630
on my bathroom mirror.

110
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:11,160
Every day I would read them

111
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,800
so that I would stay on track.

112
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,600
It made it a lot easier for
me to make the right choices

113
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,230
when I was tempted to give up.

114
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:20,060
Rule number one was save first and live on

115
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,240
what was left over.

116
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,260
By making my targets more
important than my lifestyle

117
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:26,630
it meant I never had
that much money to waste

118
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:29,000
so I made the most of every penny.

119
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:33,120
Rule number two was wait 24
hours before buying anything.

120
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:36,060
Have you ever really got
excited about buying something?

121
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:39,250
And then a few days later
that feeling just fades away

122
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:41,400
and you start to regret
what you've bought.

123
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:44,530
By waiting 24 hours to buy something

124
00:04:44,530 --> 00:04:45,920
you're able to think about it

125
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,600
with a much clearer mind.

126
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:50,120
Just doing this it saved me so much money,

127
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,260
especially when I nearly bought a jet ski.

128
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:54,180
My friend had just bought one of these

129
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:57,280
and was going out every weekend
and having a great time.

130
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,500
He gave me a go, and as you can imagine,

131
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,060
I absolutely loved it.

132
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,860
So I decided I'd buy one.

133
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:06,900
However, I waited 24 hours
and decided to just go out

134
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,530
on my friend's for the next four weekends.

135
00:05:09,530 --> 00:05:12,880
I had a great time, but
then he decided to sell it.

136
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,660
He said he was bored of it, and he would.

137
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:17,080
To be honest, I'd enjoyed riding it

138
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,270
but I felt the same.

139
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:20,100
So by waiting that 24 hours

140
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:23,550
it saved me a big impulse
purchase I would have regretted.

141
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:26,930
Rule number three was not to
fall victim to peer pressure

142
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:28,660
and lifestyle inflation.

143
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:31,340
You know, it's so easy
to increase your spending

144
00:05:31,340 --> 00:05:33,600
when you start earning
a little bit more money

145
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,440
because you wanna impress your friends

146
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,460
and your family.

147
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:38,170
But if you can resist this

148
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:40,410
you'll be able to save a lot, lot more.

149
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:43,520
I actually still shop at
the cheapest grocery stores

150
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:47,170
because I know it's all the
same stuff, Just better value.

151
00:05:47,170 --> 00:05:48,850
The next step was to start paying off

152
00:05:48,850 --> 00:05:50,690
all my high interest debts.

153
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:52,210
I had lots of different debts.

154
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:53,820
some from friends and families.

155
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,560
and others from credit cards.

156
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,370
And as balanced as it may sound

157
00:05:57,370 --> 00:06:00,940
I needed to prioritize the
highest interest debt first,

158
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:02,260
which was the credit cards.

159
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:04,550
As they were actually
costing me more money

160
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:06,980
and also destroy my credit score.

161
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:09,520
There was really no point having
money in a savings account

162
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,540
paying one to 2% interest

163
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:13,113
if I was still paying down a loan

164
00:06:13,113 --> 00:06:17,330
that was charging me
20+ % by paying that off

165
00:06:17,330 --> 00:06:21,100
that was like getting a 20%
return on the stock market,

166
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,700
which is pretty spectacular.

167
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:25,330
So if you have debts and money in savings,

168
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:26,480
then pay them down.

169
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,550
That's what I would do.

170
00:06:27,550 --> 00:06:30,330
It's the best guarantee return
you're ever likely to get.

171
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:32,030
So I stopped using my credit cards

172
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:33,880
and I set up automatic payments

173
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:36,550
so that I wouldn't be late
paying back any of my bills

174
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:39,110
the faster I could pay
these debts off the better.

175
00:06:39,110 --> 00:06:42,110
And then I could be using
my credit cards responsibly

176
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,740
to build my credit score.

177
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:46,360
In order to do this I had
to master the next step,

178
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,070
which is living frugally.

179
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:50,410
But Mark, I don't wanna live off coupons.

180
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,450
Well, lots of people
think that being frugal

181
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,470
means you have to cut back on everything

182
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:56,100
including the things you love to do

183
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:57,970
but I don't think that's true

184
00:06:57,970 --> 00:06:59,950
unless what you love is going out shopping

185
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:02,540
and spending hundreds of
dollars in the shopping mall.

186
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,970
I think you'll be just fine.

187
00:07:03,970 --> 00:07:06,140
It's all about looking for alternatives

188
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,770
that'll cost you a little bit less.

189
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:10,370
So I sat down and planned
out how I could adapt

190
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:12,960
