to be able to get to work,

202
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,750
and there wasn't a bus stop nearby.

203
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:43,000
I needed to find the best option possible.

204
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,170
So I started car hacking.

205
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:48,090
I would buy a car once it
lost most of its value,

206
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:49,690
I'd drive it around for a while

207
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:52,490
and then sell it for the exact
amount that I bought it for,

208
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:54,300
and sometimes even more.

209
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,730
So effectively the cars I drove were free.

210
00:07:56,730 --> 00:07:58,940
The only cost was fuel, how cool is that?

211
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:01,760
When I went shopping, I stopped
falling for the branding.

212
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,780
It's easy to think that
a product is better

213
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:05,520
because the packaging looks nice

214
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:08,450
but actually it's usually
just the same thing.

215
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:11,280
You just end up paying
extra for the fancy box.

216
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:14,000
Next time you're in
Walmart buying paracetamol

217
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,300
check the PL number on
the back of the box.

218
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,530
I looked the other day and the
branded cold and flu tablets

219
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:22,700
and Walmart's own brand
cold and flu tablets

220
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:24,770
